item.title: 【Live Audios (lossless)】WAV - Rolling Stones + The Linda Linda's @ SoFi Stadium 2024-07-13
item.description:
ROLLING STONES @ SOFI STADIUM 2024-07-13


THE LINDA LINDA'S @ SOFI STADIUM 2024-07-13

https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1yqt2oYjDxvQMPkTfe1bkKuZWNJ2NIjvK?usp=drive_link


This is all a blur now. I was ticketless and even considered skipping it. Eternal bucket list band and constant near miss Jesus Jones was briefly listed at some 80's festival at Pershing Square! But the promoter was obviously totally clueless, just putting names on the poster before some scab version of Asia stepped up and filled the slot.

Had a Lucky Dip courtesy of another taper. As a matter of fact I was completely outgunned on all California shows so more into just enjoying myself. Until Ridgedale this was the best of the tour. HEARTBREAKER! I was around Sec 217 for The Linda Linda's before moving into Sec C134 row 10. Had a slight confontation when Daddy and his little crotch goblin held a sign in front of my face for the third time during JJF. 3 strikes and the sign is out. Sent it flying which didn't make him happy but what's he gonna do, put the brat down and call his mom? Kid is probably better off in foster care as his current upbringing is going to get him in trouble sooner than later.

The Linda Linda's were always a bit gimmicky for me but still very happy they got the gig. I saw what I am sure was their first ever show.

item.title: 【Live Audios (lossless)】WAV - Rolling Stones @ Thunder Ridge Nature Arena, Ridgedale, MO 2024-07-21 (tour finale)
item.description:
there may already be tracked versions out there as I posted this to the blog and a Stones board right after the show

Rolling Stones @ Thunder Ridge Nature Arena, Ridgedale, MO 2024-07-21 (Raw Wav)



In 48/24

This show initially appeared the most expensive and most difficult but circumstances started trending in the other direction a few weeks before the show and it all fell together.

Had Sec 9 far side, but centered off to the front row of some center section, went to general area of seat Sec 8/9 for Keith set, drifted back during SFTD then to the front just behind pit for Satisfaction. I was a bit loose since word on the street it was being "properly archived"

May or may not be noticeable but might wanna smooth out levels a bit. Wish I got just a bit more before lights went out but some employees sat next to me and I was asking for their wristband and chatting a bit.

Love the place, love Branson. Would like to come back but the chances of finding a band that could pull in another designated driver are pretty slim.

Rolling Stones were about as good as I had ever seen them and cranked it up a notch even over the 2nd LA show.

I got the fireworks show which ran a bit longer than expected.

Anyway, do what thou wilt shall be the whole of the law. I am already thinking forward. Will deal with Samantha Fish later.
item.author: ijwthstd
